{
  "texts": [
    "The maximum number of epochs was chosen to be 20 as increasing the number of epochs did not improve the performance.",
    "The three used networks are trained with stochastic gradient descent with momentum techniques as this improves the rate of convergence and avoids getting trapped in a local minimum during convergence.",
    "Two distinct training-testing ratios are used to divide the data to prevent overfitting.",
    "The chosen training-testing ratios are 70-30 and 60-40.",
    "These splitting ratios were selected as they have been commonly used in the literature [71] [72] [73] [74] [75]."
  ]
}